# Case study reveal timer

Pre-launch case studies use a **worldwide countdown** (anchored to **IST / Asia/Kolkata**) and blur gate — not per-user `localStorage`.

## Source of truth

`src/lib/case-study-reveal-schedule.ts`

| Field | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| `mode: "daily-reset"` | Countdown runs until **IST midnight (00:00 Asia/Kolkata)**, then resets. Body **stays blurred** — the timer never unlocks content on its own. |
| `mode: "fixed"` | Legacy one-shot window from `startsAtUtc` + 24 hours. |
| Slug absent from schedule | Case study is **published** — no blur, no countdown. |

## Daily reset (default for drafts)

`cisco-policy-copilot` uses `daily-reset`. Do **not** bump `startsAtUtc` manually — the countdown resets automatically every IST day.

## Publish only when the user says so

Remove the gate **only** when the user explicitly says the case study is ready to publish, e.g.:

- “this case study is ready”
- “let’s publish this”
- “publish the case study”

Until then, keep `daily-reset` active.

### Publish checklist

1. Remove the slug from `CASE_STUDY_REVEAL_SCHEDULE`.
2. Remove `<CaseStudyRevealCountdown />` from the case study hero `metaBottom`.
3. Remove the `blur-xl` wrapper and `useCaseStudyRevealCountdownForSlug` gate in the case study component.
4. Remove the `⏳` prefix from the title in `src/lib/project-content.ts`.
5. Update the schedule table in `design.md` (§ Pre-launch reveal gate).

## Wiring

- Hook: `useCaseStudyRevealCountdownForSlug(slug)`
- UI: `<CaseStudyRevealCountdown slug="your-slug" />` in hero `metaBottom`
- Blur gate: `isRevealed` from the same hook — always `false` while `daily-reset` is active

## Do not

- Manually reset `startsAtUtc` for `daily-reset` slugs
- Per-browser countdown (`localStorage`)
- Remove the blur gate without an explicit publish request from the user
